description.text:
### Tested versions

- reproducible in 4.5.stable.mono

### System information

Godot v4.5.stable.mono - Windows 11 (build 26100) - Multi-window, 3 monitors - Direct3D 12 (Forward+) - dedicated NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4080 SUPER (NVIDIA; 32.0.15.8088) - AMD Ryzen 9 9900X 12-Core Processor (24 threads) - 61.66 GiB memory

### Issue description

I tried to override the style on a panel to achieve a mouse-over effect. When I did it in code nothing seemed to happen. Very simple code 
```
public override void _Ready()
{
	m_dropZoneHighlightStyle = ResourceLoader.Load<StyleBox>("res://resources/font_and_themes/drop_zone_highlight.tres");
	m_dropZonePanel = GetNode<Panel>("DropZonePanel");
	base._Ready();
}

// hooked up to Area2D onAreaEntered signal
public void OnEnteredDropZone(Area2D cardArea)
{
	if (m_dropZonePanel != null && m_dropZoneHighlightStyle != null)
	{
		m_dropZonePanel.AddThemeStyleboxOverride("highlight", m_dropZoneHighlightStyle);
	}
}
// hooked up to Area2D onAreaExited signal
public void OnExitedDropZone(Area2D cardArea)
{
	if (m_dropZonePanel != null)
	{
		m_dropZonePanel.RemoveThemeStyleboxOverride("highlight");
	}
}
```

This did nothing. I hit breakpoints in the entered and exited, so I knew the collision was working. The null checks also passed, and I ensured it didn't clean it up right after entering.

So I looked at the Remote view of my node tree, found the panel and manually assigned the theme override to it and that's when I got the error.

```
E 0:02:20:231   add_theme_style_override: Condition "p_style.is_null()" is true.
  <C++ Source>  scene/gui/control.cpp:3312 @ add_theme_style_override()
```


### Steps to reproduce

<img width="3839" height="2159" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/9b355ee3-bd66-43b7-a11b-32de7bead4d6" />

1. Add a panel to a scene.
2. Run Current Scene (F6)
3. Identify Theme Override Styles.
4. Assign any of the existing default StyleBoxes.
5. Note the error in the Debugger.


